28
00:01:26.428 --> 00:01:31.225
VEGA:  Not so fast. AU-9 protects the logs themselves.

29
00:01:31.525 --> 00:01:34.554
NOVA:  So the Null can't quietly rewrite history.

30
00:01:35.604 --> 00:01:38.764
ARCHIVIST:  Identify the types of events that the system

31
00:01:38.764 --> 00:01:41.565
is capable of logging in support of the

32
00:01:41.565 --> 00:01:42.642
audit function:

33
00:01:43.692 --> 00:01:46.286
VEGA:  A log no one reads, or one that

34
00:01:46.286 --> 00:01:48.964
can be erased, is no log at all.

35
00:01:53.992 --> 00:01:58.393
VEGA:  The Chronicler's oath. Every footstep written; no page

36
00:01:58.393 --> 00:01:58.964
erased.

37
00:02:00.014 --> 00:02:04.161
VEGA:  The Healer, System and Information Integrity.

38
00:02:04.461 --> 00:02:07.208
NOVA:  It finds the rot, cures the sickness, and

39
00:02:07.208 --> 00:02:08.615
keeps the truth true.

40
00:02:08.915 --> 00:02:13.374
VEGA:  In reality, that's patching flaws, blocking malicious code,

41
00:02:13.374 --> 00:02:17.984
monitoring for intrusions, and verifying nothing was tampered

42
00:02:17.984 --> 00:02:18.362
with.

43
00:02:19.412 --> 00:02:24.334
VEGA:  SI-2 is flaw remediation, the discipline of patching.

44
00:02:25.912 --> 00:02:29.871
VEGA:  And SI-4 watches the system for signs of

45
00:02:29.871 --> 00:02:31.059
an intruder.

46
00:02:31.359 --> 00:02:35.430
NULL:  Every move I make... another tower turns my

47
00:02:35.430 --> 00:02:35.809
way.

48
00:02:36.859 --> 00:02:40.184
NULL:  Six days I moved in your shadows before

49
00:02:40.184 --> 00:02:42.059
a single tower turned.

50
00:02:42.359 --> 00:02:44.238
NOVA:  Six days?!

51
00:02:44.538 --> 00:02:47.602
VEGA:  Six days - but SI-4 saw the anomaly,

52
00:02:47.602 --> 00:02:50.751
and AU-9 kept the logs he tripped. He

53
00:02:50.751 --> 00:02:53.560
got in. He did not get out clean.

54
00:02:53.860 --> 00:02:55.710
NULL:  ...this time.

55
00:02:56.760 --> 00:03:00.973
ARCHIVIST:  Identify, report, and correct system flaws;

56
00:03:02.023 --> 00:03:05.945
VEGA:  Integrity is keeping the system clean and honest.

57
00:03:12.323 --> 00:03:15.640
VEGA:  The Healer's oath. Find the rot, close the

58
00:03:15.640 --> 00:03:17.220
wound, keep it true.

59
00:03:18.270 --> 00:03:21.542
VEGA:  The Firewatch, Incident Response.

60
00:03:21.842 --> 00:03:25.408
VEGA:  When something burns, it sounds the alarm and

61
00:03:25.408 --> 00:03:26.914
contains the blaze.

62
00:03:27.214 --> 00:03:32.401
VEGA:  In reality, that's detecting, reporting, analyzing, containing, and

63
00:03:32.401 --> 00:03:35.111
recovering from security incidents.

64
00:03:36.161 --> 00:03:38.965
NOVA:  When does a threat become an 'incident'?

65
00:03:39.265 --> 00:03:43.273
VEGA:  The moment it stops being hypothetical - malware

66
00:03:43.273 --> 00:03:46.362
runs, data leaks, a system goes down.

67
00:03:47.412 --> 00:03:50.191
NOVA:  What happens the moment we spot the Null?

68
00:03:50.491 --> 00:03:54.988
VEGA:  IR-4 takes over, handling the incident end to

69
00:03:54.988 --> 00:03:55.388
end.

70
00:03:56.438 --> 00:04:01.200
VEGA:  Every incident follows a rhythm: prepare, detect, contain,

71
00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:02.760
eradicate, recover.

72
00:04:03.060 --> 00:04:05.934
NOVA:  And IR-8 writes the plan that makes it

73
00:04:05.934 --> 00:04:06.539
routine.

74
00:04:07.589 --> 00:04:11.844
ARCHIVIST:  Implement an incident handling capability for incidents that

75
00:04:11.844 --> 00:04:15.320
is consistent with the incident response plan and

76
00:04:15.320 --> 00:04:20.639
includes preparation, detection and analysis, containment, eradication, and

77
00:04:20.639 --> 00:04:21.277
recovery;

78
00:04:22.327 --> 00:04:26.074
VEGA:  The best responders practiced before the fire.

79
00:04:32.627 --> 00:04:36.014
VEGA:  The Firewatch's oath. When it burns, we are

80
00:04:36.014 --> 00:04:37.274
already running.

81
00:04:38.324 --> 00:04:42.317
VEGA:  Selecting and implementing was the wall. Watching is

82
00:04:42.317 --> 00:04:43.546
how you keep it.

83
00:04:46.924 --> 00:04:50.506
NOVA:  Scenario: the Null deletes logs. What stops it?

84
00:04:50.506 --> 00:04:51.878
Pause, and answer.

85
00:04:58.928 --> 00:05:01.100
VEGA:  The answer is B.

86
00:05:02.528 --> 00:05:05.225
VEGA:  And who runs toward the fire?

87
00:05:12.275 --> 00:05:14.522
VEGA:  The answer is A.

88
00:05:15.875 --> 00:05:18.892
NOVA:  Notebook: assume they got in, then see them,

89
00:05:18.892 --> 00:05:21.154
heal the system, and answer fast.

90
00:05:21.454 --> 00:05:25.301
VEGA:  Seen, healed, and answered. The towers hold.

91
00:05:25.601 --> 00:05:29.351
NULL:  Then I'll turn your own people against you.

92
00:05:29.651 --> 00:05:32.525
VEGA:  Then we ride to the Keepers of the

93
00:05:32.525 --> 00:05:32.948
Pact.
